<h2 id="discussion-questions">Discussion Questions</h2>
<p class="lead">Start talking. Find a conversation starter for your group.</p>

<ul>
  <li>What three things are you most tempted to do for the wrong reasons?</li>
  <li>What do you do because you feel like you‚Äôre ‚Äúsupposed to‚Äù?</li>
</ul>

<p class="lead">Start thinking. Ask questions to get your group thinking.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Is it easier to do something with the wrong heart or just not do it all? Is one always better? Why or why not?</li>
  <li>Why do you think God, through Isaiah, took specific aim at people who practiced fasting?</li>
  <li>Read Isaiah 58:5-6 AMP. Compare both kinds of fasting. What is God really getting at?</li>
</ul>

<p class="lead">Start sharing. Choose questions that create openness.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Have you ever been on the receiving end of something good that came with bad motives? What was that like?</li>
  <li>Read Isaiah 58:1-5. Is there anything you‚Äôre doing for God just to get something from Him? How do you want¬†to change?</li>
  <li>Be introspective for a minute. Why do you go to church? Come to LifeGroup? Serve? Give?</li>
  <li>Read Isaiah 58:6-14. What part of this passage stirs your heart? How will you respond?</li>
</ul>

<p class="lead">Start digging. Read Scripture about motives.</p>

